			<span class="intro-topic">Know Your Data.</span> This management application is auto-generated and is meant for simple editing of database tables only. 
			Users are expected to understand their own data and maintain proper data integrity throughout the database.
			Tables which may be edited are shown in the list to the left. 
		</p>
		
		<p>
			<span class="intro-topic">Data Entry Rules.</span> Required fields are marked with a red asterisk on data entry forms. 
			Field data types and lengths are noted next to the input fields. You will generate an error if you attempt to save
			character data to numeric fields, or if your data exceeds the stated field length.
			 
		</p>
		
		<p>
			<span class="intro-topic">Important!</span> Do not copy and paste data from Microsoft Word or Excel. 
			If you have content in Microsoft tools, first copy and paste into a simple text editor (NOTEPAD) and makes sure all 
			hidden or extraneous characters are	removed before adding it to your database.
		</p>
		
		<p>
			<span class="intro-topic">Carriage Returns.</span> The web does not recognize carriage returns - those belong in your
			word processor.  To prevent you from inadvertently breaking the production application, all carriage returns and line
			feeds will be stripped from your data upon saving to the database.  The	HTML equivalent of a new line is the &lt;br/&gt; tag.
		</p>
		
		<p>	
			<span class="intro-topic">HTML.</span> Fields that accept HTML input may be "previewed" in the admin tool, 
			but note that display styles will not necessarily match the application style sheet.  
			To author valid HTML data, look for a free HTML editor online.  Enter
			trademarks and other symbols using HTML codes. Remember - no carriage returns!  
		</p>
